article.description: — Tyson Degenhart had 24 points in Boise State's 90-66 victory against Fresno State on Saturday night.
article.headline: Boise State defeats Fresno State 90-66
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- — Tyson Degenhart had 24 points in Boise State's 90-66 victory against Fresno State on Saturday night. Degenhart had nine rebounds for the Broncos (17-8, 8-4 Mountain West Conference). O'Mar Stanley shot 6 for 8 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 4 of 6 from the free throw line to add 17 points. Max Rice was 5 of 7 shooting (3 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 13 points. The Bulldogs (11-15, 4-9) were led in scoring by Isaiah Pope, who finished with 17 points. Isaiah Hill added 15 points and six assists for Fresno State. In addition, Xavier Dusell finished with 14 points. Boise State hosts San Jose on Tuesday. Fresno State hosts San Diego State on Feb. 24. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
